<headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 09 at 1:56AM MDT  by NWS Glasgow</headline>
<description>...A strong thunderstorm will impact portions of southeastern
Garfield, southwestern McCone and northwestern Prairie Counties
through 300 AM MDT...
At 156 AM MDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Hillside, or 36 miles southeast of Jordan, moving east at 25 mph.
HAZARD...Winds in excess of 40 mph and nickel size hail.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor damage to outdoor objects is
possible.
Locations impacted include...
Flowing Wells Rest Area, Cohagen, Brockway, Hillside, Crow Rock,
Watkins and Mccloud.
MAX HAIL SIZE...0.88 IN
MAX WIND GUST...40 MPH</description>
<instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.
A Severe Thunderstorm Watch remains in effect until 300 AM MDT for
northeastern Montana.</instruction>
